['
CREATE TABLE object ( /* this is the most important table. It contains the main statistics of an object, independent of time and band */
    oid VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,  /* object identifier, from the ZTF */
    deltajd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time difference between last and first detection */
    firstmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of first detection */
    lastmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last detection */
    ndethist INTEGER,  /* number of posible detections above 3 sigma */
    ncovhist INTEGER,  /* number of visits */
    mjdstarthist DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* time of first observation even if not detected, Earliest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days]*/
    mjdendhist DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last observation even if not detected, Latest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days] */
    corrected BOOLEAN, /* whether the object was corrected */
    stellar BOOLEAN, /* whether the object is likely psf shaped */
    ndet INTEGER, /* total number of detections for the object */
    g_r_max DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r difference color at maximum */
    g_r_max_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r color at maximum*/
    g_r_mean DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r difference color */
    g_r_mean_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r color */
    meanra DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean right ascension */
    meandec DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean declination */
    sigmara DOUBLE PRECISION, /* right ascension dispersion */
    sigmadec DOUBLE PRECISION, /* declination dispersion */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR, /* correction step pipeline version */
    diffpos BOOLEAN, /* whether the first detection was positive or negative */
    reference_change BOOLEAN /* whether the reference image changes */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_ndet ON object USING btree (ndet);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_firstmjd ON object USING btree (firstmjd);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_max ON object USING btree (g_r_max);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_mean_corr ON object USING btree (g_r_mean_corr);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meanra ON object USING btree (meanra);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meandec ON object USING btree (meandec);
', 'CREATE TABLE probability ( /* this table contains the machine learning derived classification probabilities and rankings */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    class_name VARCHAR, /* name of the class */
    classifier_name VARCHAR, /* name of the classifier */
    classifier_version VARCHAR, /* version of the classiifer */
    probability DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* probability of the class given a classifier and version */
    ranking INTEGER NOT NULL, /* class probability ranking (1 is the most likely class) */
    PRIMARY KEY (oid, class_name, classifier_name, classifier_version)
);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_oid ON probability USING hash (oid);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_probability ON probability USING btree (probability);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_ranking ON probability USING btree (ranking);
CREATE INDEX ix_classification_rank1 ON probability USING btree (ranking) WHERE (ranking = 1);
', 'CREATE TABLE detection (  /* this table contains information about the object detections, or its light curve. Avoid doing filters on this table in any parameter other than oid */
    candid BIGINT PRIMARY KEY, /* unique candidate identifier */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    mjd DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* time of detection in modified julian date */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* filter identifier  (1=g; 2=r; 3=i)*/
    pid FLOAT NOT NULL, /* program identifier */
    diffmaglim DOUBLE PRECISION, /* limiting difference magnitud */
    isdiffpos INTEGER NOT NULL, /* whether the difference is positive or negative */
    nid INTEGER, /* unique night identifier */
    ra DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred right ascension */
    dec DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred declination */
    magpsf DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* point spread function (psf) difference magnitude */
    sigmapsf DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* psf difference magnitude error */
    magap DOUBLE PRECISION, /* aperture difference magnitude */
    sigmagap DOUBLE PRECISION, /* aperture difference magnitud error */
    distnr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* distance to the nearest source in the reference image */
    rb DOUBLE PRECISION, /* ZTF real bogus score */
    rbversion VARCHAR, /* version of the ZTF real bogus score */
    drb DOUBLE PRECISION, /* ZTF deep learning based real bogus score */
    drbversion VARCHAR, /* versio  of the ZTF deep learning based real bogus score */
    magapbig DOUBLE PRECISION, /* large aperture magnitude */
    sigmagapbig DOUBLE PRECISION, /* large aperture magnitude error */
    rfid INTEGER, /* identifier of the reference image used for the difference image */
    magpsf_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* apparent magnitude (corrected difference magnitude) */
    sigmapsf_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming point like source */
    sigmapsf_corr_ext DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming extended source */
    corrected BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object’s magnitude was corrected */
    dubious BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object is dubious or not */
    parent_candid BIGINT, /* identifier of the candidate where this information was generated (this happens if the given detection does not pass the real bogus filter, but a later detection does */
    has_stamp BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the candidate has an associated image stamp (same as before */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR NOT NULL /* identifier of the correction step */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_ndetection_oid ON detection USING hash (oid);
', '
CREATE TABLE taxonomy (
    classifier_name VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY, /* name of the taxonomy */
    classifier_version VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY, /* taxonomy version */
    classes VARCHAR[] NOT NULL /* classes in the hierarchical form they are computed */
);
']

sql_query: # Step 1: Sub-query for Probability Tableprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE ranking = 1AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'AND class_name = 'AGN'"""# Step 2: Sub-query for r Band Variabilityr_band_variability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 2AND oid IN ({})""".format(probability_subquery)# Step 3: Sub-query for g Band Non-variabilityg_band_non_variability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 1AND oid IN ({})""".format(probability_subquery)# Step 4: Combine Feature Sub-queriescombined_features_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM ({}) AS r_bandINTERSECTSELECT oidFROM ({}) AS g_band""".format(r_band_variability_subquery, g_band_non_variability_subquery)# Step 5: Final Query Constructionfinal_query = """SELECT o.*FROM object oWHERE o.oid IN ({})ORDER BY o.oid ASC""".format(combined_features_subquery)# Final query assignmentfull_query = final_query

sql_query: # Step 1: Sub-query for Probability Tableprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'AND ranking = 1AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Sub-query for r Band Variabilityr_band_variability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 2AND name = 'variability_feature_name' -- Replace with actual feature name indicating variabilityAND oid IN ({})""".format(probability_subquery)# Step 3: Sub-query for g Band Non-variabilityg_band_non_variability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 1AND name = 'variability_feature_name' -- Replace with actual feature name indicating variabilityAND value < threshold_value -- Replace with actual threshold for non-variabilityAND oid IN ({})""".format(probability_subquery)# Step 4: Combine Sub-queriescombined_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM ({}) AS r_bandINTERSECTSELECT oidFROM ({}) AS g_band""".format(r_band_variability_subquery, g_band_non_variability_subquery)# Step 5: Final Queryfinal_query = """SELECT *FROM featureWHERE oid IN ({})ORDER BY value ASC, oid""".format(combined_subquery)# Assign the final query to the variable full_queryfull_query = final_query

sql_query: # Step 1: Sub-query for Probability Tableprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'AND ranking = 1AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Sub-query for r Band Variabilityr_band_variability_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 2AND value > 0  -- Assuming a positive value indicates variabilityAND oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Step 3: Sub-query for g Band Non-variabilityg_band_non_variability_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 1AND value = 0  -- Assuming zero value indicates no variabilityAND oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Step 4: Combine Sub-queriescombined_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM ({r_band_variability_subquery}) AS r_bandINTERSECTSELECT oidFROM ({g_band_non_variability_subquery}) AS g_band"""# Step 5: Final Query Constructionfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.*FROM object oWHERE o.oid IN ({combined_subquery})ORDER BY o.oid"""# Assign the final query to the variable full_queryfull_query = final_query

sql_query: # Sub-query for AGN Classificationagn_classification = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'AND ranking = 1AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Sub-query for r Band Variabilityr_band_variability = f"""SELECT f.oidFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({agn_classification}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.fid = 2AND f.value IS NOT NULL"""# Sub-query for g Band Non-variabilityg_band_non_variability = f"""SELECT f.oidFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({agn_classification}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.fid = 1AND f.value IS NULL"""# Combine Feature Sub-queriescombined_features = f"""SELECT oidFROM (    {r_band_variability}    UNION    {g_band_non_variability}) AS combinedINTERSECTSELECT oidFROM (    {r_band_variability}    INTERSECT    {g_band_non_variability}) AS intersected"""# Final Queryfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.*FROM object oWHERE o.oid IN ({combined_features})ORDER BY o.oid ASC"""full_query = final_query

sql_query: # Step 1: Sub-query for Probability Tableprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'AND ranking = 1"""# Step 2: Sub-query for r Band Variabilityr_band_variability_subquery = f"""SELECT f.oidFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.fid = 2AND f.name = 'variability_feature_name'  -- Replace with actual feature name indicating variabilityAND f.value > 0  -- Replace with actual condition indicating variability"""# Step 3: Sub-query for g Band Non-variabilityg_band_non_variability_subquery = f"""SELECT f.oidFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.fid = 1AND (f.name = 'variability_feature_name' AND f.value = 0)  -- Replace with actual feature name and condition indicating no variability"""# Step 4: Combine Sub-queriescombined_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM ({r_band_variability_subquery}) AS r_bandINTERSECTSELECT oidFROM ({g_band_non_variability_subquery}) AS g_band"""# Step 5: Final Query Constructionfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.*FROM object oWHERE o.oid IN ({combined_subquery})ORDER BY o.oid"""full_query = final_query

sql_query: # Step 1: Sub-query for AGN Classificationagn_classification_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'AND ranking = 1AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Sub-query for r Band Variabilityr_band_variability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 2AND name = 'variability'AND value > 0AND oid IN ({agn_classification_subquery})"""# Step 3: Sub-query for g Band Non-variabilityg_band_non_variability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM featureWHERE fid = 1AND name = 'variability'AND value = 0AND oid IN ({agn_classification_subquery})"""# Step 4: Combine Feature Sub-queriescombined_features_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM (    {r_band_variability_subquery}    UNION    {g_band_non_variability_subquery}) AS combinedINTERSECTSELECT oidFROM (    {r_band_variability_subquery}    INTERSECT    {g_band_non_variability_subquery}) AS intersected"""# Step 5: Final Queryfinal_query = """SELECT o.*FROM object oWHERE o.oid IN ({combined_features_subquery})ORDER BY o.oid"""# Combine all steps into the final queryfull_query = final_query.format(    agn_classification_subquery=agn_classification_subquery,    r_band_variability_subquery=r_band_variability_subquery,    g_band_non_variability_subquery=g_band_non_variability_subquery,    combined_features_subquery=combined_features_subquery)

sql_query: # Step 1: Sub-query for Probability Tableprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Sub-query for r Band Variabilityr_band_variability_subquery = """SELECT f.oid, f.name, f.valueFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.fid = 2  AND f.value IS NOT NULL  -- Assuming a non-null value indicates variability"""# Step 3: Sub-query for g Band Non-variabilityg_band_non_variability_subquery = """SELECT f.oid, f.name, f.valueFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.fid = 1  AND f.value IS NULL  -- Assuming a null value indicates no variability"""# Step 4: Combine Sub-queriescombined_subquery = """SELECT oid, name, valueFROM (  {r_band_variability_subquery}  UNION  {g_band_non_variability_subquery}) AS combined"""# Step 5: Final Query Constructionfinal_query = """SELECT *FROM ({combined_subquery}) AS finalWHERE oid IN (  SELECT oid  FROM ({r_band_variability_subquery}) AS r_band  INTERSECT  SELECT oid  FROM ({g_band_non_variability_subquery}) AS g_band)ORDER BY oid, value ASC"""# Combine all steps into the final queryfull_query = final_query.format(    probability_subquery=probability_subquery,    r_band_variability_subquery=r_band_variability_subquery,    g_band_non_variability_subquery=g_band_non_variability_subquery,    combined_subquery=combined_subquery)

sql_query: -- Step 1: Sub-query for Probability Tableprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE ranking = 1AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'AND oid IN ('ZTF17aaadpsi', 'ZTF19aaduncs', 'ZTF18abnvehl', 'ZTF19abrqsxy', 'ZTF19aaduodl', 'ZTF19aadovdv', 'ZTF18aammkke', 'ZTF18abtriul', 'ZTF17aabwtky', 'ZTF18abwjpfy')"""-- Step 2: Sub-query for Amplitude Featureamplitude_subquery = """SELECT f.oid, f.name, f.value, f.fid, f.versionFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.name = 'Amplitude'"""-- Step 3: Sub-query for Multiband_period Featuremultiband_period_subquery = """SELECT f.oid, f.name, f.value, f.fid, f.versionFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON f.oid = p.oidWHERE f.name = 'Multiband_period'"""-- Step 4: Combine Feature Sub-queries with UNIONunion_query = """({amplitude_subquery})UNION({multiband_period_subquery})"""-- Step 5: Intersect Feature Sub-queriesintersect_query = """({amplitude_subquery})INTERSECT({multiband_period_subquery})"""-- Step 6: Filter Combined Resultsfinal_query = """SELECT u.*FROM ({union_query}) uWHERE u.oid IN ({intersect_query})"""-- Final Query Constructionfull_query = f"""{final_query}"""

['
CREATE TABLE object ( /* this is the most important table. It contains the main statistics of an object, independent of time and band */
    oid VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,  /* object identifier, from the ZTF */
    deltajd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time difference between last and first detection */
    firstmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of first detection */
    lastmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last detection */
    ndethist INTEGER,  /* number of posible detections above 3 sigma */
    ncovhist INTEGER,  /* number of visits */
    mjdstarthist DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* time of first observation even if not detected, Earliest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days]*/
    mjdendhist DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last observation even if not detected, Latest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days] */
    corrected BOOLEAN, /* whether the object was corrected */
    stellar BOOLEAN, /* whether the object is likely psf shaped */
    ndet INTEGER, /* total number of detections for the object */
    g_r_max DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r difference color at maximum */
    g_r_max_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r color at maximum*/
    g_r_mean DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r difference color */
    g_r_mean_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r color */
    meanra DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean right ascension */
    meandec DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean declination */
    sigmara DOUBLE PRECISION, /* right ascension dispersion */
    sigmadec DOUBLE PRECISION, /* declination dispersion */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR, /* correction step pipeline version */
    diffpos BOOLEAN, /* whether the first detection was positive or negative */
    reference_change BOOLEAN /* whether the reference image changes */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_ndet ON object USING btree (ndet);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_firstmjd ON object USING btree (firstmjd);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_max ON object USING btree (g_r_max);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_mean_corr ON object USING btree (g_r_mean_corr);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meanra ON object USING btree (meanra);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meandec ON object USING btree (meandec);
', 'CREATE TABLE feature ( /* table with features for a given object, each row contains one feature per object */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    name VARCHAR NOT NULL, /* name of the feature */
    value DOUBLE PRECISION, /* value of the feature */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* which bandpass this is based (1: g, 2: r, 3: i, 12: gr, 13: gi, 23: ri, 123: gri, ) */
    version VARCHAR REFERENCES feature_version(version) NOT NULL, /* version of the features (see table feature_version) */
    PRIMARY KEY (oid, name, fid, version)
);
CREATE INDEX ix_feature_oid_2 ON feature USING hash (oid);
']

sql_query: # Step 1: Filter by Classificationprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Filter by Light Curve Durationobject_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM objectWHERE (lastmjd - firstmjd) >= 365"""# Step 3: Filter by Number of Detections and Magnitude Variationsmagstat_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM magstatWHERE (fid = 1 AND ndet >= 20 AND (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) > 1)   OR (fid = 2 AND ndet >= 20 AND (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) > 0.5)"""# Step 4: Retrieve Featuresfeature_subquery = f"""SELECT oid, value, name, version, fid AS feature_fidFROM featureWHERE oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Step 5: Combine Subqueries and Final Selectionfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.feature_fid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,       m.magmax_corr, m.magmin_corr, (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) AS delta_magFROM ({probability_subquery}) AS pJOIN ({object_subquery}) AS o ON p.oid = o.oidJOIN ({magstat_subquery}) AS m ON o.oid = m.oidJOIN ({feature_subquery}) AS f ON o.oid = f.oidWHERE m.fid IN (1, 2)"""full_query = final_query

['CREATE TABLE probability ( /* this table contains the machine learning derived classification probabilities and rankings */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    class_name VARCHAR, /* name of the class */
    classifier_name VARCHAR, /* name of the classifier */
    classifier_version VARCHAR, /* version of the classiifer */
    probability DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* probability of the class given a classifier and version */
    ranking INTEGER NOT NULL, /* class probability ranking (1 is the most likely class) */
    PRIMARY KEY (oid, class_name, classifier_name, classifier_version)
);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_oid ON probability USING hash (oid);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_probability ON probability USING btree (probability);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_ranking ON probability USING btree (ranking);
CREATE INDEX ix_classification_rank1 ON probability USING btree (ranking) WHERE (ranking = 1);
', 'CREATE TABLE detection (  /* this table contains information about the object detections, or its light curve. Avoid doing filters on this table in any parameter other than oid */
    candid BIGINT PRIMARY KEY, /* unique candidate identifier */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    mjd DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* time of detection in modified julian date */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* filter identifier  (1=g; 2=r; 3=i)*/
    pid FLOAT NOT NULL, /* program identifier */
    diffmaglim DOUBLE PRECISION, /* limiting difference magnitud */
    isdiffpos INTEGER NOT NULL, /* whether the difference is positive or negative */
    nid INTEGER, /* unique night identifier */

sql_query: # Step 1: Filter objects classified as AGN with a probability greater than 0.6agn_prob_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Filter objects with light curves covering at least one year and at least 20 detectionsobject_filter_subquery = f"""SELECT o.oid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndetFROM object oWHERE o.deltajd >= 365  AND o.ndet >= 20  AND o.oid IN ({agn_prob_subquery})"""# Step 3: Calculate magnitude variations in g and r bandsmagstat_filter_subquery = f"""SELECT m.oid, m.fid, m.magmax_corr, m.magmin_corr, (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) AS delta_magFROM magstat mWHERE ((m.fid = 1 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 1) OR       (m.fid = 2 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 0.5))  AND m.oid IN ({object_filter_subquery})"""# Step 4: Retrieve features for the filtered objectsfeature_subquery = f"""SELECT f.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fid AS feature_fidFROM feature fWHERE f.oid IN ({object_filter_subquery})"""# Step 5: Combine resultsfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.feature_fid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,        m.magmax_corr, m.magmin_corr, m.delta_magFROM ({object_filter_subquery}) oINNER JOIN ({magstat_filter_subquery}) m ON o.oid = m.oidINNER JOIN ({feature_subquery}) f ON o.oid = f.oid"""# Final queryfull_query = final_query

sql_query: # Step 1: Subquery for Probabilityprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Subquery for Featurefeature_subquery = """SELECT oid, value, name, version, fid AS feature_fidFROM featureWHERE oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Step 3: Subquery for Magstatmagstat_subquery = """SELECT oid, fid, magmax_corr, magmin_corr, (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) AS delta_magFROM magstatWHERE ndet >= 20  AND ((fid = 1 AND (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) > 1) OR (fid = 2 AND (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) > 0.5))  AND oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Step 4: Final Queryfinal_query = """SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.feature_fid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,        m.magmax_corr, m.magmin_corr, m.delta_magFROM object oINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON o.oid = p.oidINNER JOIN ({feature_subquery}) f ON o.oid = f.oidINNER JOIN ({magstat_subquery}) m ON o.oid = m.oidWHERE (o.mjdendhist - o.mjdstarthist) >= 365"""# Combine all subqueries into the final queryfull_query = final_query.format(probability_subquery=probability_subquery, feature_subquery=feature_subquery, magstat_subquery=magstat_subquery)

sql_query: # Step 1: Sub-query for Classificationclassification_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Sub-query for Light Curve Conditionslight_curve_subquery = f"""SELECT o.oidFROM object oJOIN magstat m_g ON o.oid = m_g.oid AND m_g.fid = 1JOIN magstat m_r ON o.oid = m_r.oid AND m_r.fid = 2WHERE o.lastmjd - o.firstmjd >= 365  AND (m_g.ndet >= 20 OR m_r.ndet >= 20)  AND m_g.magmax_corr - m_g.magmin_corr > 1  AND m_r.magmax_corr - m_r.magmin_corr > 0.5  AND o.oid IN ({classification_subquery})"""# Step 3: Sub-query for Feature Extractionfeature_subquery = f"""SELECT f.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fidFROM feature fWHERE f.oid IN ({light_curve_subquery})"""# Step 4: Combine Resultsfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fid AS feature_fid,       o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,       m_g.magmax_corr AS g_magmax_corr, m_g.magmin_corr AS g_magmin_corr,       m_r.magmax_corr AS r_magmax_corr, m_r.magmin_corr AS r_magmin_corr,       (m_g.magmax_corr - m_g.magmin_corr) AS g_delta_mag,       (m_r.magmax_corr - m_r.magmin_corr) AS r_delta_magFROM ({feature_subquery}) fJOIN object o ON f.oid = o.oidJOIN magstat m_g ON o.oid = m_g.oid AND m_g.fid = 1JOIN magstat m_r ON o.oid = m_r.oid AND m_r.fid = 2"""full_query = final_query

sql_query: # Step 1: Filter Objects by Classification and Probabilityprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Step 2: Filter Objects by Light Curve Duration and Detectionsobject_subquery = f"""SELECT oid, meanra, meandec, ndetFROM objectWHERE deltajd >= 365  AND ndet >= 20  AND oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Step 3: Filter by Magnitude Variations in Specific Bandsmagstat_g_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM magstatWHERE fid = 1  AND magmax_corr - magmin_corr > 1  AND oid IN ({object_subquery})"""magstat_r_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM magstatWHERE fid = 2  AND magmax_corr - magmin_corr > 0.5  AND oid IN ({object_subquery})"""# Step 4: Retrieve Required Informationfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fid AS feature_fid,       o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,       mg.magmax_corr, mg.magmin_corr, (mg.magmax_corr - mg.magmin_corr) AS delta_magFROM ({object_subquery}) oINNER JOIN feature f ON o.oid = f.oidINNER JOIN magstat mg ON o.oid = mg.oidWHERE o.oid IN ({magstat_g_subquery})  AND o.oid IN ({magstat_r_subquery})"""full_query = final_query

sql_query: # Sub-query for Probabilityprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Sub-query for Objectobject_subquery = f"""SELECT o.oid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndetFROM object oINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON o.oid = p.oidWHERE o.deltajd >= 365"""# Sub-query for Magstatmagstat_subquery = f"""SELECT m.oid, m.fid AS magstat_fid, m.magmax_corr, m.magmin_corr,        (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) AS delta_magFROM magstat mINNER JOIN ({object_subquery}) o ON m.oid = o.oidWHERE m.ndet >= 20  AND ((m.fid = 1 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 1) OR       (m.fid = 2 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 0.5))"""# Sub-query for Featurefeature_subquery = f"""SELECT f.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fid AS feature_fidFROM feature fINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON f.oid = p.oid"""# Final Queryfull_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.feature_fid,        o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,        m.magmax_corr, m.magmin_corr, m.delta_magFROM ({object_subquery}) oINNER JOIN ({magstat_subquery}) m ON o.oid = m.oidINNER JOIN ({feature_subquery}) f ON o.oid = f.oid"""

sql_query: -- Step 1: Sub-query for Probability Tableprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""-- Step 2: Sub-query for Magstat Tablemagstat_subquery = """SELECT oid, fid, magmax_corr, magmin_corr, ndetFROM magstatWHERE corrected = TRUE  AND ndet >= 20  AND ((fid = 1 AND magmax_corr - magmin_corr > 1) OR (fid = 2 AND magmax_corr - magmin_corr > 0.5))  AND oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""-- Step 3: Sub-query for Object Tableobject_subquery = """SELECT oid, meanra, meandec, ndetFROM objectWHERE deltajd >= 365  AND oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""-- Step 4: Sub-query for Feature Tablefeature_subquery = """SELECT oid, value, name, version, fidFROM featureWHERE oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""-- Step 5: Combine Resultsfinal_query = """SELECT p.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fid AS feature_fid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,        m.magmax_corr, m.magmin_corr, (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) AS delta_magFROM ({probability_subquery}) AS pINNER JOIN ({magstat_subquery}) AS m ON p.oid = m.oidINNER JOIN ({object_subquery}) AS o ON p.oid = o.oidINNER JOIN ({feature_subquery}) AS f ON p.oid = f.oid"""

sql_query: # Sub-query for Probabilityprobability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'AGN'  AND probability > 0.6  AND ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'"""# Sub-query for Featurefeature_subquery = """SELECT oid, value, name, version, fid AS feature_fidFROM featureWHERE oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Main Querymain_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.feature_fid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,       mg_g.magmax_corr AS g_magmax_corr, mg_g.magmin_corr AS g_magmin_corr,       mg_r.magmax_corr AS r_magmax_corr, mg_r.magmin_corr AS r_magmin_corr,       (mg_g.magmax_corr - mg_g.magmin_corr) AS g_delta_mag,       (mg_r.magmax_corr - mg_r.magmin_corr) AS r_delta_magFROM object oINNER JOIN magstat mg_g ON o.oid = mg_g.oid AND mg_g.fid = 1INNER JOIN magstat mg_r ON o.oid = mg_r.oid AND mg_r.fid = 2INNER JOIN ({feature_subquery}) f ON o.oid = f.oidWHERE o.deltajd >= 365  AND (mg_g.ndet >= 20 OR mg_r.ndet >= 20)  AND (mg_g.magmax_corr - mg_g.magmin_corr > 1)  AND (mg_r.magmax_corr - mg_r.magmin_corr > 0.5)"""# Final Queryfull_query = main_query

sql_query: -- Subquery to filter probability table for class 'SN' with highest rankingWITH prob_subquery AS (    SELECT oid, probability    FROM probability    WHERE class_name = 'SN'      AND ranking = 1      AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'),-- Subquery to filter objects detected in the first 2 days of Septemberobject_subquery AS (    SELECT o.oid, o.firstmjd    FROM object o    JOIN prob_subquery p ON o.oid = p.oid    WHERE o.firstmjd BETWEEN 2459458.5 AND 2459460.5 -- Julian dates for September 1st and 2nd, 2023),-- Subquery to identify fast risers using magstatfast_risers AS (    SELECT m.oid, m.fid AS magstat_fid, m.dmdt_first    FROM magstat m    JOIN object_subquery o ON m.oid = o.oid    WHERE m.dmdt_first > 0 -- Assuming positive dmdt_first indicates fast risers)-- Final query to retrieve required informationSELECT o.oid, p.probability, d.fid, d.diffmaglim, f.magstat_fid, f.dmdt_firstFROM object_subquery oJOIN prob_subquery p ON o.oid = p.oidJOIN fast_risers f ON o.oid = f.oidJOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oidLEFT JOIN non_detection nd ON o.oid = nd.oidORDER BY o.oidLIMIT 100

sql_query: -- Subquery 1: Get oids with highest probability in stamp classifier for class 'SN'WITH highest_prob_sn AS (    SELECT oid, probability    FROM probability    WHERE classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'      AND class_name = 'SN'      AND ranking = 1),-- Subquery 2: Get oids with first detection in the first 2 days of Septemberfirst_detection_september AS (    SELECT oid    FROM object    WHERE firstmjd >= 2459458.5 AND firstmjd < 2459460.5 -- Julian dates for September 1 and 2, 2023),-- Subquery 3: Get oids that qualify as fast risersfast_risers AS (    SELECT oid, fid AS magstat_fid, dmdt_first    FROM magstat    WHERE dmdt_first > 0 -- Assuming positive dmdt_first indicates fast risers),-- Combine the subqueries to get the final resultfinal_result AS (    SELECT o.oid, hp.probability, d.fid, d.diffmaglim, nd.fid AS non_detection_fid, nd.mjd, fr.magstat_fid, fr.dmdt_first    FROM highest_prob_sn hp    INNER JOIN first_detection_september fds ON hp.oid = fds.oid    INNER JOIN fast_risers fr ON hp.oid = fr.oid    INNER JOIN detection d ON hp.oid = d.oid    INNER JOIN non_detection nd ON hp.oid = nd.oid)-- Select the final result, order by oid, and limit to 100 rowsSELECT *FROM final_resultORDER BY oidLIMIT 100

sql_query: -- Subquery to filter probability table for highest probability for class 'SN' in the stamp classifierWITH prob_subquery AS (    SELECT oid, probability    FROM probability    WHERE ranking = 1      AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'      AND class_name = 'SN'),-- Subquery to filter object table for first detection in the first 2 days of Septemberobject_subquery AS (    SELECT o.oid, o.firstmjd    FROM object o    INNER JOIN prob_subquery p ON o.oid = p.oid    WHERE o.firstmjd BETWEEN 2459458.5 AND 2459460.5 -- Julian dates for September 1st and 2nd, 2023),-- Subquery to filter magstat table for fast risersfast_risers_subquery AS (    SELECT m.oid, m.fid AS magstat_fid, m.dmdt_first    FROM magstat m    INNER JOIN object_subquery os ON m.oid = os.oid    WHERE m.dmdt_first IS NOT NULL -- Assuming fast risers have a non-null dmdt_first)-- Final query to join with non_detection and detection tablesSELECT o.oid, p.probability, nd.fid, nd.diffmaglim, fr.magstat_fid, fr.dmdt_firstFROM object oINNER JOIN prob_subquery p ON o.oid = p.oidINNER JOIN fast_risers_subquery fr ON o.oid = fr.oidLEFT JOIN non_detection nd ON o.oid = nd.oidORDER BY o.oidLIMIT 100

sql_query: -- Subquery to get oids with highest probability for class 'SN' in the stamp classifierprobability_subquery = """SELECT oid, probabilityFROM probabilityWHERE ranking = 1  AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'  AND class_name = 'SN'"""-- Subquery to get oids with first detection in the first 2 days of Septemberobject_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM objectWHERE firstmjd BETWEEN 59834 AND 59835"""-- Subquery to get oids that qualify as fast risersfast_risers_subquery = """SELECT oid, fid AS magstat_fid, dmdt_firstFROM magstatWHERE dmdt_first IS NOT NULL"""-- Final query combining all subqueriesfull_query = """SELECT o.oid, p.probability, d.fid, d.isdiffpos, m.magstat_fid, m.dmdt_firstFROM ({probability_subquery}) pINNER JOIN ({object_subquery}) o ON p.oid = o.oidINNER JOIN ({fast_risers_subquery}) m ON o.oid = m.oidINNER JOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oidORDER BY o.oidLIMIT 100""".format(probability_subquery=probability_subquery, object_subquery=object_subquery, fast_risers_subquery=fast_risers_subquery)

sql_query: # Subquery for probability table to get objects with highest probability for class 'SN'probability_subquery = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'SN'AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'AND ranking = 1"""# Subquery for object table to filter objects with first detection in the first two days of Septemberobject_subquery = f"""SELECT oidFROM objectWHERE firstmjd BETWEEN 2459458.5 AND 2459460.5AND oid IN ({probability_subquery})"""# Subquery for magstat table to identify fast risersmagstat_subquery = f"""SELECT oid, fid AS magstat_fid, dmdt_firstFROM magstatWHERE dmdt_first IS NOT NULLAND oid IN ({object_subquery})"""# Subquery for non_detection table to get non-detectionsnon_detection_subquery = f"""SELECT oid, fid, mjd, diffmaglimFROM non_detectionWHERE oid IN ({object_subquery})"""# Final query combining all subqueriesfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, p.probability, nd.fid, nd.diffmaglim, ms.magstat_fid, ms.dmdt_firstFROM ({object_subquery}) oJOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oidJOIN ({non_detection_subquery}) nd ON o.oid = nd.oidJOIN ({magstat_subquery}) ms ON o.oid = ms.oidWHERE p.class_name = 'SN'AND p.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'AND p.ranking = 1ORDER BY o.oidLIMIT 100"""full_query = final_query

sql_query: # Subquery 1: Get objects with highest probability in the stamp classifier for class 'SN'subquery1 = """SELECT oid, probabilityFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'SN'  AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'  AND ranking = 1"""# Subquery 2: Get objects with first detection in the first 2 days of Septembersubquery2 = """SELECT oidFROM objectWHERE firstmjd BETWEEN 59800 AND 59802  -- Assuming 59800 is the MJD for September 1st, 2023"""# Subquery 3: Get objects that qualify as fast riserssubquery3 = """SELECT oid, fid AS magstat_fid, dmdt_firstFROM magstatWHERE dmdt_first > 0  -- Assuming a positive dmdt_first indicates a fast riser"""# Final Query: Combine all subqueries and retrieve the required informationfull_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, p.probability, d.fid, d.isdiffpos, m.magstat_fid, m.dmdt_firstFROM ({subquery1}) pINNER JOIN ({subquery2}) o ON p.oid = o.oidINNER JOIN ({subquery3}) m ON o.oid = m.oidINNER JOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oidORDER BY o.oidLIMIT 100"""
tab_schema:
['
CREATE TABLE object ( /* this is the most important table. It contains the main statistics of an object, independent of time and band */
    oid VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,  /* object identifier, from the ZTF */
    deltajd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time difference between last and first detection */
    firstmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of first detection */
    lastmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last detection */
    ndethist INTEGER,  /* number of posible detections above 3 sigma */
    ncovhist INTEGER,  /* number of visits */
    mjdstarthist DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* time of first observation even if not detected, Earliest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days]*/
    mjdendhist DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last observation even if not detected, Latest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days] */
    corrected BOOLEAN, /* whether the object was corrected */
    stellar BOOLEAN, /* whether the object is likely psf shaped */
    ndet INTEGER, /* total number of detections for the object */
    g_r_max DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r difference color at maximum */
    g_r_max_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r color at maximum*/
    g_r_mean DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r difference color */
    g_r_mean_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r color */
    meanra DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean right ascension */
    meandec DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean declination */
    sigmara DOUBLE PRECISION, /* right ascension dispersion */
    sigmadec DOUBLE PRECISION, /* declination dispersion */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR, /* correction step pipeline version */
    diffpos BOOLEAN, /* whether the first detection was positive or negative */
    reference_change BOOLEAN /* whether the reference image changes */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_ndet ON object USING btree (ndet);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_firstmjd ON object USING btree (firstmjd);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_max ON object USING btree (g_r_max);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_mean_corr ON object USING btree (g_r_mean_corr);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meanra ON object USING btree (meanra);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meandec ON object USING btree (meandec);
', 'CREATE TABLE probability ( /* this table contains the machine learning derived classification probabilities and rankings */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    class_name VARCHAR, /* name of the class */
    classifier_name VARCHAR, /* name of the classifier */
    classifier_version VARCHAR, /* version of the classiifer */
    probability DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* probability of the class given a classifier and version */
    ranking INTEGER NOT NULL, /* class probability ranking (1 is the most likely class) */
    PRIMARY KEY (oid, class_name, classifier_name, classifier_version)
);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_oid ON probability USING hash (oid);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_probability ON probability USING btree (probability);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_ranking ON probability USING btree (ranking);
CREATE INDEX ix_classification_rank1 ON probability USING btree (ranking) WHERE (ranking = 1);
', 'CREATE TABLE detection (  /* this table contains information about the object detections, or its light curve. Avoid doing filters on this table in any parameter other than oid */
    candid BIGINT PRIMARY KEY, /* unique candidate identifier */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    mjd DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* time of detection in modified julian date */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* filter identifier  (1=g; 2=r; 3=i)*/
    pid FLOAT NOT NULL, /* program identifier */
    diffmaglim DOUBLE PRECISION, /* limiting difference magnitud */
    isdiffpos INTEGER NOT NULL, /* whether the difference is positive or negative */
    nid INTEGER, /* unique night identifier */
    ra DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred right ascension */
    dec DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred declination */
    magpsf DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* point spread function (psf) difference magnitude */
    sigmapsf DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* psf difference magnitude error */
    magap DOUBLE PRECISION, /* aperture difference magnitude */
    sigmagap DOUBLE PRECISION, /* aperture difference magnitud error */
    distnr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* distance to the nearest source in the reference image */
    rb DOUBLE PRECISION, /* ZTF real bogus score */
    rbversion VARCHAR, /* version of the ZTF real bogus score */
    drb DOUBLE PRECISION, /* ZTF deep learning based real bogus score */
    drbversion VARCHAR, /* versio  of the ZTF deep learning based real bogus score */
    magapbig DOUBLE PRECISION, /* large aperture magnitude */
    sigmagapbig DOUBLE PRECISION, /* large aperture magnitude error */
    rfid INTEGER, /* identifier of the reference image used for the difference image */
    magpsf_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* apparent magnitude (corrected difference magnitude) */
    sigmapsf_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming point like source */
    sigmapsf_corr_ext DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming extended source */
    corrected BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object’s magnitude was corrected */
    dubious BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object is dubious or not */
    parent_candid BIGINT, /* identifier of the candidate where this information was generated (this happens if the given detection does not pass the real bogus filter, but a later detection does */
    has_stamp BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the candidate has an associated image stamp (same as before */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR NOT NULL /* identifier of the correction step */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_ndetection_oid ON detection USING hash (oid);
', 'CREATE TABLE magstat ( /* different statistics for the object divided by band or filter */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* band or filter identifier (1=g; 2=r; 3=i) */
    stellar BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether we believe the object is stellar */
    corrected BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object’s light curve has been corrected */
    ndet INTEGER NOT NULL, /* the object number of detection in the given band */
    ndubious INTEGER NOT NULL, /* the points in the light curve in the given band that we don’t trust  */
    dmdt_first DOUBLE PRECISION, /* lower limit for the the rate of magnitude change at detection in the given band */
    dm_first DOUBLE PRECISION, /* change in magnitude with respect to the last non detection at detection in the given band */
    sigmadm_first DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error in the change of magnitude w.r.t. the last detection in the given band */
    dt_first DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time between the last non detection and the first detection for the given band */
    magmean DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean difference magnitude for the given band */
    magmedian DOUBLE PRECISION, /* median difference magnitude for the given band */
    magmax DOUBLE PRECISION, /* maximum difference magnitude for the given band */
    magmin DOUBLE PRECISION, /* minimum difference magnitude for the given band */
    magsigma DOUBLE PRECISION, /* dispersion of the difference magnitude for the given band */
    maglast DOUBLE PRECISION, /* last difference magnitude for the given band */
    magfirst DOUBLE PRECISION, /* first difference magnitude for the given band */
    magmean_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean apparent (corrected) magnitude for the given band */
    magmedian_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* median apparent (corrected) magnitude for the given band */
    magmax_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* maximum apparent (corrected) magnitude for the given band */
    magmin_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* minimum apparent (corrected) magnitude for the given band */
    magsigma_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* dispersion of the apparent (corrected) magnitude for the given band */
    maglast_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* last apparent (corrected) magnitude for the given band */
    magfirst_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean apparent (corrected) magnitude for the given band */
    firstmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of first detection for the given band */
    lastmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last detection for the given band */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR NOT NULL, /* correction step id */
    saturation_rate DOUBLE PRECISION /* saturation level for the given band */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_dmdt_first ON magstat USING btree (dmdt_first);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_firstmjd ON magstat USING btree (firstmjd);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_lastmjd ON magstat USING btree (lastmjd);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_magmean ON magstat USING btree (magmean);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_magmin ON magstat USING btree (magmin);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_magfirst ON magstat USING btree (magfirst);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_ndet ON magstat USING btree (ndet);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_maglast ON magstat USING btree (maglast);
CREATE INDEX ix_magstats_oid ON magstat USING hash (oid);
', 'CREATE TABLE feature ( /* table with features for a given object, each row contains one feature per object */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    name VARCHAR NOT NULL, /* name of the feature */
    value DOUBLE PRECISION, /* value of the feature */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* which bandpass this is based (1: g, 2: r, 3: i, 12: gr, 13: gi, 23: ri, 123: gri, ) */
    version VARCHAR REFERENCES feature_version(version) NOT NULL, /* version of the features (see table feature_version) */
    PRIMARY KEY (oid, name, fid, version)
);
CREATE INDEX ix_feature_oid_2 ON feature USING hash (oid);
']
label: advanced

sql_query: # Subquery 1: Get objects with the highest probability in the stamp classifier for class 'SN'subquery1 = """SELECT oid, probabilityFROM probabilityWHERE classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'  AND class_name = 'SN'  AND ranking = 1"""# Subquery 2: Get objects with first detection in the first 2 days of Septembersubquery2 = """SELECT oidFROM objectWHERE firstmjd >= 2459458.5 AND firstmjd < 2459460.5"""# Subquery 3: Get objects that qualify as fast riserssubquery3 = """SELECT oid, fid AS magstat_fid, dmdt_firstFROM magstatWHERE dmdt_first > 0.1  -- Assuming a threshold for fast risers"""# Subquery 4: Get non-detections for the selected objectssubquery4 = """SELECT oid, fid, mjd, diffmaglimFROM non_detection"""# Final query: Combine all subqueries and apply final filtersfinal_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, p.probability, nd.fid, nd.mjd, nd.diffmaglim, m.magstat_fid, m.dmdt_firstFROM ({subquery1}) pINNER JOIN ({subquery2}) o ON p.oid = o.oidINNER JOIN ({subquery3}) m ON o.oid = m.oidINNER JOIN ({subquery4}) nd ON o.oid = nd.oidORDER BY o.oidLIMIT 100"""full_query = final_query
label: advanced

sql_query: -- Subquery to filter objects with the highest probability in the stamp classifier for class 'SN'WITH prob_subquery AS (    SELECT p.oid, p.probability    FROM probability p    INNER JOIN object o ON p.oid = o.oid    WHERE p.ranking = 1      AND p.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'      AND p.class_name = 'SN'      AND o.firstmjd BETWEEN 59832 AND 59834 -- First 2 days of September 2023),-- Subquery to filter fast risers using magstatfast_risers AS (    SELECT m.oid, m.fid AS magstat_fid, m.dmdt_first    FROM magstat m    WHERE m.dmdt_first > 0 -- Assuming positive dmdt_first indicates fast risers),-- Subquery to get light curves including non-detectionslight_curves AS (    SELECT d.oid, d.fid, d.diffmaglim, d.rfid    FROM detection d    UNION    SELECT nd.oid, nd.fid, nd.diffmaglim, NULL AS rfid    FROM non_detection nd)-- Final query to combine all subqueriesSELECT ps.oid, ps.probability, lc.fid, lc.diffmaglim, fr.magstat_fid, fr.dmdt_firstFROM prob_subquery psINNER JOIN fast_risers fr ON ps.oid = fr.oidINNER JOIN light_curves lc ON ps.oid = lc.oidORDER BY ps.oidLIMIT 100

sql_query: # Sub-query to filter objects based on the date range and number of detectionsobject_subquery = """SELECT oid, meanra, meandec, ndet, firstmjdFROM objectWHERE firstmjd BETWEEN 59265 AND 59301  -- Corresponds to March 1st, 2021 to April 1st, 2021AND ndet <= 1"""# Sub-query to filter probabilities for asteroids with the stamp classifierprobability_subquery = """SELECT oid, class_name, probabilityFROM probabilityWHERE class_name = 'asteroid'AND probability > 0.7AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'AND ranking = 1"""# Final query joining the object and probability sub-queriesfull_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet, o.firstmjd, p.class_name, p.probabilityFROM ({object_subquery}) oINNER JOIN ({probability_subquery}) p ON o.oid = p.oid"""

sql_query: subquery_detection = """SELECT d.oid, d.candid, d.fid, d.mjd, d.magpsf, d.sigmapsf, d.has_stamp, d.drbFROM detection dWHERE d.oid IN ('ZTF23aavzgjg', 'ZTF23aaynzyk', 'ZTF23aavqxos', 'ZTF23aaknyni',                 'ZTF23aavsdtc', 'ZTF18aandkua', 'ZTF23aaxfewt', 'ZTF23aavshwi',                 'ZTF22aawasao', 'ZTF23aaxgvnt')AND d.drb > 0.5"""subquery_join_ps1_ztf = f"""SELECT det.oid, det.candid, det.fid, det.mjd, det.magpsf, det.sigmapsf, det.has_stamp, det.drb, pz.sgscore1, pz.distpsnr1FROM ({subquery_detection}) detINNER JOIN ps1_ztf pz ON det.oid = pz.oid AND det.candid = pz.candidWHERE pz.sgscore1 < 0.5 OR pz.distpsnr1 < 1"""full_query = f"""SELECT *FROM ({subquery_join_ps1_ztf}) final_resultORDER BY final_result.oid, final_result.candid"""

sql_query: # Sub-query to filter objects based on first detection time and spatial locationobject_filter_query = """SELECT oid, meanra, meandecFROM objectWHERE firstmjd BETWEEN 59623 AND 60032  -- February 13, 2023 to September 10, 2023 in MJDAND point(meanra, meandec) <@ '((-20, -20), (-2, -20), (20, 1), (10, 10))'::polygon"""# Sub-query to filter objects classified as Supernovaeprobability_filter_query = """SELECT oidFROM probabilityWHERE ranking = 1AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'AND class_name IN ('SNIa', 'SNIbc', 'SNII', 'SLSN')"""# Final query combining the object and probability filtersfull_query = f"""SELECT o.oid, o.meanra, o.meandecFROM ({object_filter_query}) AS oINNER JOIN ({probability_filter_query}) AS p ON o.oid = p.oid"""

    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    mjd DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* time of detection in modified julian date */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* filter identifier  (1=g; 2=r; 3=i)*/
    pid FLOAT NOT NULL, /* program identifier */
    diffmaglim DOUBLE PRECISION, /* limiting difference magnitud */
    isdiffpos INTEGER NOT NULL, /* whether the difference is positive or negative */
    nid INTEGER, /* unique night identifier */
    ra DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred right ascension */
    dec DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred declination */
    magpsf DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* point spread function (psf) difference magnitude */
    sigmapsf DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* psf difference magnitude error */
    magap DOUBLE PRECISION, /* aperture difference magnitude */
    sigmagap DOUBLE PRECISION, /* aperture difference magnitud error */
    distnr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* distance to the nearest source in the reference image */
    rb DOUBLE PRECISION, /* ZTF real bogus score */
    rbversion VARCHAR, /* version of the ZTF real bogus score */
    drb DOUBLE PRECISION, /* ZTF deep learning based real bogus score */
    drbversion VARCHAR, /* versio  of the ZTF deep learning based real bogus score */
    magapbig DOUBLE PRECISION, /* large aperture magnitude */
    sigmagapbig DOUBLE PRECISION, /* large aperture magnitude error */
    rfid INTEGER, /* identifier of the reference image used for the difference image */
    magpsf_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* apparent magnitude (corrected difference magnitude) */
    sigmapsf_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming point like source */
    sigmapsf_corr_ext DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming extended source */
    corrected BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object’s magnitude was corrected */
    dubious BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object is dubious or not */
    parent_candid BIGINT, /* identifier of the candidate where this information was generated (this happens if the given detection does not pass the real bogus filter, but a later detection does */
    has_stamp BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the candidate has an associated image stamp (same as before */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR NOT NULL /* identifier of the correction step */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_ndetection_oid ON detection USING hash (oid);
']

sql_query: -- Subquery to calculate distance and filter objects within specified radiiWITH distance_filtered_objects AS (    SELECT         oid,         ndet,         meanra,         meandec,         firstmjd,         lastmjd,        -- Calculate angular distance for id_1        DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(15.954)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(15.954)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 354.67)))) * 3600 AS distance_id_1,        -- Calculate angular distance for id_2        DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(1.00331)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(1.00331)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 20.7993)))) * 3600 AS distance_id_2    FROM         object    WHERE         -- Filter objects within 30 arcsec of id_1 or 20 arcsec of id_2        (DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(15.954)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(15.954)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 354.67)))) * 3600 <= 30)        OR        (DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(1.00331)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(1.00331)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 20.7993)))) * 3600 <= 20))-- Final query to select required columns and sort by last detection dateSELECT     'id_1' AS input_object_id,    354.67 AS input_ra,    15.954 AS input_dec,    30/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid AS ztf_identifier,    ndet AS number_of_detections,    meanra AS mean_ra,    meandec AS mean_dec,    firstmjd AS first_detection_date,    lastmjd AS last_detection_dateFROM     distance_filtered_objectsWHERE     distance_id_1 <= 30UNIONSELECT     'id_2' AS input_object_id,    20.7993 AS input_ra,    1.00331 AS input_dec,    20/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid AS ztf_identifier,    ndet AS number_of_detections,    meanra AS mean_ra,    meandec AS mean_dec,    firstmjd AS first_detection_date,    lastmjd AS last_detection_dateFROM     distance_filtered_objectsWHERE     distance_id_2 <= 20ORDER BY     last_detection_date DESC

sql_query: # Subquery to find ZTF objects within 30 arcsec of id_1subquery_id_1 = """SELECT oid, ndet, meanra, meandec, firstmjd, lastmjdFROM objectWHERE (DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(15.954)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(15.954)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 354.67)))) * 3600) <= 30"""# Subquery to find ZTF objects within 20 arcsec of id_2subquery_id_2 = """SELECT oid, ndet, meanra, meandec, firstmjd, lastmjdFROM objectWHERE (DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(1.00331)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(1.00331)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 20.7993)))) * 3600) <= 20"""# Final query combining both subqueries and selecting required columnsfull_query = f"""SELECT     'id_1' AS identifier,     354.67 AS ra,     15.954 AS dec,     30/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid AS ztf_identifier,     ndet AS number_of_detections,     meanra AS mean_ra,     meandec AS mean_dec,     firstmjd AS first_detection_dateFROM ({subquery_id_1}) AS subquery1UNIONSELECT     'id_2' AS identifier,     20.7993 AS ra,     1.00331 AS dec,     20/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid AS ztf_identifier,     ndet AS number_of_detections,     meanra AS mean_ra,     meandec AS mean_dec,     firstmjd AS first_detection_dateFROM ({subquery_id_2}) AS subquery2ORDER BY lastmjd DESC"""

sql_query: # Subquery to calculate distance and filter objects within specified arcsec from id_1 and id_2distance_filter_query = """SELECT     oid,     ndet,     meanra,     meandec,     firstmjd,     lastmjd,    SQRT(POW((meanra - 354.67) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 15.954), 2)) * 3600 AS distance_id_1,    SQRT(POW((meanra - 20.7993) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 1.00331), 2)) * 3600 AS distance_id_2FROM     objectWHERE     (SQRT(POW((meanra - 354.67) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 15.954), 2)) * 3600 <= 30)    OR     (SQRT(POW((meanra - 20.7993) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 1.00331), 2)) * 3600 <= 20)"""# Final query to select required columns and sort by last detection datefinal_query = f"""SELECT     'id_1' AS input_identifier,     354.67 AS input_ra,     15.954 AS input_dec,     30/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid AS ztf_identifier,     ndet AS number_of_detections,     meanra AS mean_ra,     meandec AS mean_dec,     firstmjd AS first_detection_dateFROM     ({distance_filter_query}) AS filtered_objectsWHERE     distance_id_1 <= 30/3600.0UNIONSELECT     'id_2' AS input_identifier,     20.7993 AS input_ra,     1.00331 AS input_dec,     20/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid AS ztf_identifier,     ndet AS number_of_detections,     meanra AS mean_ra,     meandec AS mean_dec,     firstmjd AS first_detection_dateFROM     ({distance_filter_query}) AS filtered_objectsWHERE     distance_id_2 <= 20/3600.0ORDER BY     lastmjd DESC"""full_query = final_query

sql_query: # Subquery to calculate distance and filter objects within specified radiidistance_subquery = """SELECT oid, meanra, meandec, ndet, firstmjd, lastmjd,       SQRT(POW((meanra - 354.67) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 15.954), 2)) AS distance_id_1,       SQRT(POW((meanra - 20.7993) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 1.00331), 2)) AS distance_id_2FROM objectWHERE (SQRT(POW((meanra - 354.67) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 15.954), 2)) <= 0.008333)   OR (SQRT(POW((meanra - 20.7993) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)), 2) + POW((meandec - 1.00331), 2)) <= 0.005556)"""# Main query to select required columns and sort by last detection datemain_query = f"""SELECT     'id_1' AS input_identifier, 354.67 AS input_ra, 15.954 AS input_dec, 0.008333 AS search_radius,    oid AS ztf_identifier, ndet AS number_of_detections, meanra AS mean_ra, meandec AS mean_dec, firstmjd AS first_detection_dateFROM ({distance_subquery}) AS filtered_objectsWHERE distance_id_1 <= 0.008333UNIONSELECT     'id_2' AS input_identifier, 20.7993 AS input_ra, 1.00331 AS input_dec, 0.005556 AS search_radius,    oid AS ztf_identifier, ndet AS number_of_detections, meanra AS mean_ra, meandec AS mean_dec, firstmjd AS first_detection_dateFROM ({distance_subquery}) AS filtered_objectsWHERE distance_id_2 <= 0.005556ORDER BY lastmjd DESC"""# Final queryfull_query = main_query

sql_query: # Subquery for objects within 30 arcsec of id_1subquery_id_1 = """SELECT oid, ndet, meanra, meandec, firstmjd, lastmjdFROM objectWHERE (DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(15.954)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(15.954)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 354.67)))) * 3600) <= 30"""# Subquery for objects within 20 arcsec of id_2subquery_id_2 = """SELECT oid, ndet, meanra, meandec, firstmjd, lastmjdFROM objectWHERE (DEGREES(ACOS(SIN(RADIANS(1.00331)) * SIN(RADIANS(meandec)) + COS(RADIANS(1.00331)) * COS(RADIANS(meandec)) * COS(RADIANS(meanra - 20.7993)))) * 3600) <= 20"""# Final query combining both subqueries and sorting by last detection datefull_query = f"""SELECT     'id_1' AS identifier,     354.67 AS ra,     15.954 AS dec,     30/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid,     ndet,     meanra,     meandec,     firstmjdFROM ({subquery_id_1}) AS subquery1UNIONSELECT     'id_2' AS identifier,     20.7993 AS ra,     1.00331 AS dec,     20/3600.0 AS search_radius_deg,    oid,     ndet,     meanra,     meandec,     firstmjdFROM ({subquery_id_2}) AS subquery2ORDER BY lastmjd DESC"""

sql_query: SELECT     dq.oid,     dq.candid,     dq.xpos,     dq.ypos,     dq.scorrFROM     dataquality dqWHERE     dq.oid IN ('ZTF20acwrybw', 'ZTF22abugigx')     AND dq.fid = 2 -- r-band filter
tab_schema:
['
CREATE TABLE dataquality (
    candid BIGINT PRIMARY KEY, /* unique identifier for the subtraction candidate */
    oid VARCHAR NOT NULL, /* unique identifier for this object */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* Filter ID (1=g; 2=r; 3=i) */
    xpos DOUBLE PRECISION, /* x-image position of candidate [pixels] */
    ypos DOUBLE PRECISION, /* y-image position of candidate [pixels] */
    chipsf DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Reduced chi-square for PSF-fit */
    sky DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Local sky background estimate [DN] */
    fwhm DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Full Width Half Max assuming a Gaussian core, from SExtractor [pixels] */
    classtar DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Star/Galaxy classification score from SExtractor */
    mindtoedge DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Distance to nearest edge in image [pixels] */
    seeratio DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: difffwhm / fwhm */
    aimage DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Windowed profile RMS afloat major axis from SExtractor [pixels] */
    bimage DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Windowed profile RMS afloat minor axis from SExtractor [pixels] */
    aimagerat DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: aimage / fwhm */
    bimagerat DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: bimage / fwhm */
    nneg INTEGER, /* number of negative pixels in a 5 x 5 pixel stamp */
    nbad INTEGER, /* number of prior-tagged bad pixels in a 5 x 5 pixel stamp */
    sumrat DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: sum(pixels) / sum(abs(pixels)) in a 5 x 5 pixel stamp where stamp is first median-filtered to mitigate outliers */
    scorr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Peak-pixel signal-to-noise ratio in point source matched-filtered detection image */
    dsnrms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: D/stddev(D) on event position where D = difference image */
    ssnrms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: S/stddev(S) on event position where S = image of convolution: D (x) PSF(D) */
    magzpsci DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Magnitude zero point for photometry estimates [mag] */
    magzpsciunc DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Magnitude zero point uncertainty (in magzpsci) [mag] */
    magzpscirms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* RMS (deviation from average) in all differences between instrumental photometry and matched photometric calibrators from science image processing [mag] */
    nmatches INTEGER, /* Number of PS1 photometric calibrators used to calibrate science image from science image processing */
    clrcoeff DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Color coefficient from linear fit from photometric calibration of science image */
    clrcounc DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Color coefficient uncertainty from linear fit (corresponding to clrcoeff) */
    zpclrcov DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Covariance in magzpsci and clrcoeff from science image processing [mag^2] */
    zpmed DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Magnitude zero point from median of all differences between instrumental photometry and matched photometric calibrators from science image processing [mag] */
    clrmed DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Median color of all PS1 photometric calibrators used from science image processing [mag]: for filter (fid) = 1, 2, 3, PS1 color used = g-r, g-r, r-i respectively */
    clrrms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* RMS color (deviation from average) of all PS1 photometric calibrators used from science image processing [mag] */
    exptime DOUBLE PRECISION /* Integration time of camera exposure [sec] */
    FOREIGN KEY (candid, oid) REFERENCES detection(candid, oid)
);
']

    xpos DOUBLE PRECISION, /* x-image position of candidate [pixels] */
    ypos DOUBLE PRECISION, /* y-image position of candidate [pixels] */
    chipsf DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Reduced chi-square for PSF-fit */
    sky DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Local sky background estimate [DN] */
    fwhm DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Full Width Half Max assuming a Gaussian core, from SExtractor [pixels] */
    classtar DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Star/Galaxy classification score from SExtractor */
    mindtoedge DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Distance to nearest edge in image [pixels] */
    seeratio DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: difffwhm / fwhm */
    aimage DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Windowed profile RMS afloat major axis from SExtractor [pixels] */
    bimage DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Windowed profile RMS afloat minor axis from SExtractor [pixels] */
    aimagerat DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: aimage / fwhm */
    bimagerat DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: bimage / fwhm */
    nneg INTEGER, /* number of negative pixels in a 5 x 5 pixel stamp */
    nbad INTEGER, /* number of prior-tagged bad pixels in a 5 x 5 pixel stamp */
    sumrat DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: sum(pixels) / sum(abs(pixels)) in a 5 x 5 pixel stamp where stamp is first median-filtered to mitigate outliers */
    scorr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Peak-pixel signal-to-noise ratio in point source matched-filtered detection image */
    dsnrms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Ratio: D/stddev(D) on event position where D = difference image */

    magzpsci DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Magnitude zero point for photometry estimates [mag] */
    magzpsciunc DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Magnitude zero point uncertainty (in magzpsci) [mag] */
    magzpscirms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* RMS (deviation from average) in all differences between instrumental photometry and matched photometric calibrators from science image processing [mag] */
    nmatches INTEGER, /* Number of PS1 photometric calibrators used to calibrate science image from science image processing */
    clrcoeff DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Color coefficient from linear fit from photometric calibration of science image */
    clrcounc DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Color coefficient uncertainty from linear fit (corresponding to clrcoeff) */
    zpclrcov DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Covariance in magzpsci and clrcoeff from science image processing [mag^2] */
    zpmed DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Magnitude zero point from median of all differences between instrumental photometry and matched photometric calibrators from science image processing [mag] */
    clrmed DOUBLE PRECISION, /* Median color of all PS1 photometric calibrators used from science image processing [mag]: for filter (fid) = 1, 2, 3, PS1 color used = g-r, g-r, r-i respectively */
    clrrms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* RMS color (deviation from average) of all PS1 photometric calibrators used from science image processing [mag] */
    exptime DOUBLE PRECISION /* Integration time of camera exposure [sec] */
    FOREIGN KEY (candid, oid) REFERENCES detection(candid, oid)
);
']

    classifier_version VARCHAR, /* version of the classiifer */
    probability DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* probability of the class given a classifier and version */
    ranking INTEGER NOT NULL, /* class probability ranking (1 is the most likely class) */
    PRIMARY KEY (oid, class_name, classifier_name, classifier_version)
);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_oid ON probability USING hash (oid);

sql_query: subquery_object = """SELECT oid FROM object WHERE firstmjd > 60310"""
tab_schema:
['
CREATE TABLE object ( /* this is the most important table. It contains the main statistics of an object, independent of time and band */
    oid VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,  /* object identifier, from the ZTF */
    deltajd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time difference between last and first detection */
    firstmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of first detection */
    lastmjd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last detection */
    ndethist INTEGER,  /* number of posible detections above 3 sigma */
    ncovhist INTEGER,  /* number of visits */
    mjdstarthist DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* time of first observation even if not detected, Earliest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days]*/
    mjdendhist DOUBLE PRECISION, /* time of last observation even if not detected, Latest Julian date of epoch corresponding to ndethist [days] */
    corrected BOOLEAN, /* whether the object was corrected */
    stellar BOOLEAN, /* whether the object is likely psf shaped */
    ndet INTEGER, /* total number of detections for the object */
    g_r_max DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r difference color at maximum */
    g_r_max_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* g-r color at maximum*/
    g_r_mean DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r difference color */
    g_r_mean_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* mean g-r color */
    meanra DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean right ascension */
    meandec DOUBLE PRECISION,  /* mean declination */
    sigmara DOUBLE PRECISION, /* right ascension dispersion */
    sigmadec DOUBLE PRECISION, /* declination dispersion */
    step_id_corr VARCHAR, /* correction step pipeline version */
    diffpos BOOLEAN, /* whether the first detection was positive or negative */
    reference_change BOOLEAN /* whether the reference image changes */
);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_ndet ON object USING btree (ndet);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_firstmjd ON object USING btree (firstmjd);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_max ON object USING btree (g_r_max);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_g_r_mean_corr ON object USING btree (g_r_mean_corr);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meanra ON object USING btree (meanra);
CREATE INDEX ix_object_meandec ON object USING btree (meandec);
', 'CREATE TABLE probability ( /* this table contains the machine learning derived classification probabilities and rankings */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    class_name VARCHAR, /* name of the class */
    classifier_name VARCHAR, /* name of the classifier */
    classifier_version VARCHAR, /* version of the classiifer */
    probability DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* probability of the class given a classifier and version */
    ranking INTEGER NOT NULL, /* class probability ranking (1 is the most likely class) */
    PRIMARY KEY (oid, class_name, classifier_name, classifier_version)
);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_oid ON probability USING hash (oid);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_probability ON probability USING btree (probability);
CREATE INDEX ix_probabilities_ranking ON probability USING btree (ranking);
CREATE INDEX ix_classification_rank1 ON probability USING btree (ranking) WHERE (ranking = 1);
', 'CREATE TABLE forced_photometry ( /* this table contains information about the forced photometry */
    pid BIGINT PRIMARY KEY, /* unique candidate identifier */
    oid VARCHAR REFERENCES object(oid), /* unique object identifier */
    mjd DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* time of detection in modified julian date */
    fid INTEGER NOT NULL, /* filter identifier  (1=g; 2=r; 3=i)*/
    ra DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred right ascension */
    dec DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* inferred declination */
    mag DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* point spread function (psf) difference magnitude */
    e_mag DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* psf difference magnitude error */
    mag_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* apparent magnitude (corrected difference magnitude) */
    e_mag_corr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming point like source */
    e_mag_corr_ext DOUBLE PRECISION, /* error of the apparent magnitude assuming extended source */
    isdiffpos INTEGER NOT NULL, /* whether the difference is positive or negative */
    corrected BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object’s magnitude was corrected */
    dubious BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the object is dubious or not */
    parent_candid BIGINT, /* identifier of the candidate where this information was generated (this happens if the given detection does not pass the real bogus filter, but a later detection does */
    has_stamp BOOLEAN NOT NULL, /* whether the candidate has an associated image stamp (same as before */
    field INTEGER, /* field identifier */
    rcid INTEGER, /* reference catalog identifier */
    rfid INTEGER, /* identifier of the reference image used for the difference image */
    sciinpseeing DOUBLE PRECISION, /* seeing in the science image */
    scibckgnd DOUBLE PRECISION, /* background in the science image */
    scisigpix DOUBLE PRECISION, /* sigma per pixel in the science image */
    magzpsci DOUBLE PRECISION, /* zero point magnitude in the science image */
    magzpsciunc DOUBLE PRECISION, /* uncertainty in the zero point magnitude in the science image */
    magzpscirms DOUBLE PRECISION, /* rms of the zero point magnitude in the science image */
    clrcoeff DOUBLE PRECISION, /* color correction coefficient */
    clrcounc DOUBLE PRECISION, /* uncertainty in the color correction coefficient */
    exptime DOUBLE PRECISION, /* exposure time */
    adpctdif1 DOUBLE PRECISION, /* percentage difference in aperture photometry */
    adpctdif2 DOUBLE PRECISION, /* percentage difference in aperture photometry */
    diffmaglim DOUBLE PRECISION, /* limiting difference magnitude */
    programid INTEGER, /* program identifier */
    procstatus VARCHAR, /* processing status */
    distnr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* distance to the nearest source in the reference image */
    ranr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* right ascension of the nearest source in the reference image */
    decnr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* declination of the nearest source in the reference image */
    magnr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* magnitude of the nearest source in the reference image */
    sigmagnr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* magnitude error of the nearest source in the reference image */
    chinr DOUBLE PRECISION, /* chi of the nearest source in the reference image */
    sharpnr DOUBLE PRECISION /* sharpness of the nearest source in the reference image */
);']

sql_query: SELECT     oid_catalog,     ra,     dec,     w1mpro,     w1sigmpro,     w2mpro,     w2sigmpro,     j_m_2mass,     j_msig_2massFROM     allwiseWHERE     q3c_radial_query(ra, dec, 23.6488, 30.7314, 1/3600.0) -- 1 arcsec converted to degrees
tab_schema:
['
CREATE TABLE allwise (
    oid_catalog VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY, /* object Id inside catalog, correspond to column: designation  in ALLWISE : Sexagesimal, equatorial position-based source name in the form: hhmmss.ss+ddmmss.s. The full naming convention for AllWISE Source Catalog sources has the form "WISEA  Jhhmmss.ss+ddmmss.s," where "WISEA" indicates the source is from the AllWISE Source Catalog, and "J" indicates the position is J2000. The "WISEA" acronym is not listed explicitly in the designation column. */
    ra DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* J2000 right ascension with respect to the 2MASS PSC reference frame from the non-moving source extraction. */
    dec DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* J2000 declination with respect to the 2MASS PSC reference frame from the non-moving source extraction. */
    w1mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* W1 magnitude measured with profile-fitting photometry, or the magnitude of the 95% confidence brightness upper limit if the W1 flux measurement has SNR<2. This column is null if the source is nominally detected in W1, but no useful brightness estimate could be made. */
    w2mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1mpro */
    w3mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1mpro */
    w4mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1mpro */
    w1sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* W1 profile-fit photometric measurement uncertainty in mag units. This column is null if the W1 profile-fit magnitude is a 95% confidence upper limit or if the source is not measurable. */
    w2sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1sigmpro */
    w3sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1sigmpro */
    w4sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1sigmpro */
    j_m_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* 2MASS J-band magnitude or magnitude upper limit of the associated 2MASS PSC source. This column is "null" if there is no associated 2MASS PSC source or if the 2MASS PSC J-band magnitude entry is "null". */
    h_m_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to j_m_2mass */
    k_m_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to j_m_2mass */
    j_msig_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* 2MASS J-band corrected photometric uncertainty of the associated 2MASS PSC source. This column is "null" if there is no associated 2MASS PSC source or if the 2MASS PSC J-band uncertainty entry is "null". */
    h_msig_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to j_msig_2mass */
    k_msig_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION /* analogous to j_msig_2mass */
);

CREATE INDEX ix_allwise_dec ON allwise USING btree (dec);
CREATE INDEX ix_allwise_ra ON allwise USING btree (ra);
']

The full naming convention for AllWISE Source Catalog sources has the form "WISEA  Jhhmmss.ss+ddmmss.s," where "WISEA" indicates the source is from the AllWISE Source Catalog, and "J" indicates the position is J2000. The "WISEA" acronym is not listed explicitly in the designation column. */
    ra DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* J2000 right ascension with respect to the 2MASS PSC reference frame from the non-moving source extraction. */
    dec DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL, /* J2000 declination with respect to the 2MASS PSC reference frame from the non-moving source extraction. */
    w1mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* W1 magnitude measured with profile-fitting photometry, or the magnitude of the 95% confidence brightness upper limit if the W1 flux measurement has SNR<2. This column is null if the source is nominally detected in W1, but no useful brightness estimate could be made. */
    w2mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1mpro */
    w3mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1mpro */
    w4mpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1mpro */
    w1sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* W1 profile-fit photometric measurement uncertainty in mag units. This column is null if the W1 profile-fit magnitude is a 95% confidence upper limit or if the source is not measurable. */
    w2sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1sigmpro */
    w3sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1sigmpro */
    w4sigmpro DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to w1sigmpro */
    j_m_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* 2MASS J-band magnitude or magnitude upper limit of the associated 2MASS PSC source. This column is "null" if there is no associated 2MASS PSC source or if the 2MASS PSC J-band magnitude entry is "null". */
    h_m_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to j_m_2mass */
    k_m_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to j_m_2mass */
    j_msig_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* 2MASS J-band corrected photometric uncertainty of the associated 2MASS PSC source. This column is "null" if there is no associated 2MASS PSC source or if the 2MASS PSC J-band uncertainty entry is "null". */
    h_msig_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION, /* analogous to j_msig_2mass */
    k_msig_2mass DOUBLE PRECISION /* analogous to j_msig_2mass */
);

CREATE INDEX ix_allwise_dec ON allwise USING btree (dec);
CREATE INDEX ix_allwise_ra ON allwise USING btree (ra);
']
